headline: IBM Stock Falls. Why Strong Earnings Weren’t Enough.
summary: International Business Machines  reported better-than-expected earnings results for its latest quarter.  Revenue came in at $16.3 billion, which was ahead of analysts’ expectations for $16.1 billion.  “New innovation, the strength and diversity of our portfolio, and our disciplined execution led to acceleration in revenue growth and profit in the quarter,” IBM Chief Financial Officer James Kavanaugh said in the press release.
